  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: The person profile screen can always be scrolled even though everything is visible on the screen. I'd have scroll only when it's needed (content does not fit the screen). \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nScreen should not be scrollable when content fits the screen.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nScreen can be scrolled. But, the good thing is that the scroll bounces back, so there is no way to end up with empty screen. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status on iOS\r\n- Go to a profile of contact\r\n- Scroll it\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: introduced in #3570 \r\n* Operating System: **iOS only**. Works on Android\r\n* Tested on iPhone 6",
